- HTML have not case sensitive
E.g. - <HTML> same as </html>


Heading - Easy simple tags (no extra efforts)
HTML Heading includes Element whole "<h1> to </h1>" 
 
 - HTML element => <h1>heading</h1>
 - Tag name => <h1>.....</h1>
   
- Tag have Properties or Attributes => title="heading one"
  E.g. -
   <h1 title="heading one">heading</h1>  <== all includes are html elements (<h1....to..../h1>
                    title="heading one"  <== Properties or Attributes

*NOTE :- tag close In html (</h1>) its not create problem, but in react or other lang create PROBLEM

- Nested heading - 
<h2>Heading <span>Two</span></h2> <== span is also tag 

Tags or headings are so many attributes -
- Anchor tag
  E.g. <a href=""></a> -> by default attribute href
	     - href compulsory values when not filed then not go any site
  Emmet shortcut --> a:
  E.g. -
  <a href="http://" target="" rel="noopener noreferrer"></a>

*NOTE :- Suggestion in Vs code in target property --> Ctr + Space 

-------- DOCUMENTATION -------------
Meanings of any tags -> search on web E.g. --> "a tag mdn"
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a
------------------------------------

- Every tag or every element having some compulsory attribute or not compulsory 
   - not compulsory attribute <title> tag - we write or not any difference
	 - compulsory attribute <a> tag - for working we write compulsory attribute
	
*NOTE :- Intersting thing
  - after write <h1 title="heading one">heading</h1>
  - & hover mouse on heading then hover show heading one
  - modify all tooltips through or CSS through

E.g.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
      <meta charset="UTF-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
      <title>HTML tutorial</title>
</head>
<body>
      <!-- Element includes <h1> to </h1> -->
      <h1 title="heading one">Heading</h1>
      <h2>Heading <span>Two</span> </h2>
      <a href="#">Google</a>
      <a href="http://" target="" rel="noopener noreferrer"></a>
</body>
</html>


Shortcut for - 
Duplicate values -->
  Alt + Shift + down key
Multi changes at time -->
  Click + Alt + Click

Shortcut for Paragraph -
Emmet use Text through Paragraph ---> <p>lorem20</p>

Q. - How to work paragraph tag?
=>
  Paragraphs are block-level elements, and notably will automatically close if another block-level element is parsed before the closing </p> tag.

Break line -
Break line best practice for JS (ideal in JS) ==> <br />

Horizontal line --> <hr>

Q. How to solve Classic Poem Problem ?
=>
  In paragraph classic Poem problem - 
  Below solution is not solve poem problem
  E.g. -
  <p>
            line 1 <br>
            line 2 <br>
            <br>
            line 3
            lin3 4
 </p>

  pre tag solve poem problem -
  E.g. -
  <pre>
            line 1
            line 2
          
            line 3
            lin3 4
  </pre>

pre tag -
 - browser default formating
 E.g. in Js concept -
   <pre>console.log("hello")</pre>

E.g.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
      <meta charset="UTF-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
      <title>Heading</title>
</head>
<body>
      <h1>Heading one</h1> <!-- duplicate value alt+shift+downkey -->
      <h2>Heading two</h2> <!-- duplicate value click+alt+click -->
      <h3>Heading three</h3>
      <h4>Heading four</h4>
      <h5>Heading five</h5>
      <h6>Heading six</h6>

      <p>Lorem ipsum dolor, sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Eligendi, laborum sequi adipisci 
            <hr>
            <br />
            impedit dignissimos veniam sapiente recusandae quidem magnam sunt.</p>

            <!-- Not show as a poem 
            <p>
                  line 1 <br>
                  line 2 <br>
                  <br>
                  line 3
                  lin3 4
            </p>
            -->

            <!-- Use pre tag solve poem problem -->
            <pre>
                  line 1
                  line 2
                
                  line 3
                  lin3 4
            </pre>
      <hr>
      <br />
      
      <pre>console.log("hello")</pre>

</body>
</html>
